{"id":827,"date":"2017-03-15T19:59:59","date_gmt":"2017-03-15T19:59:59","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=827"},"modified":"2020-08-31T11:51:17","modified_gmt":"2020-08-31T11:51:17","slug":"invoicing-project","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/invoicing-project\/","title":{"rendered":"Invoicing Project"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Invoicing project is recomended to do only from the project area via the Invoice Project button on the top right side to keep track of all invoices created for&nbsp;the project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"modal-title wp-block-heading\">Project Invoice Info<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>There is 3 types of how the invoice items will be structure when invoicing the project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Single Line &#8211; <strong>Not applied if project Billing Type is Task Hours<\/strong>\n<ol>\n<li><b>Item name:<\/b> Project name<\/li>\n<li><b>Description:<\/b> All tasks + total logged time per task<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/li><li>Task Per Item &#8211; All billable tasks per item &#8211;<strong>&nbsp;(Not applied if Billing type is Fixed Cost)<\/strong>\n<ol>\n<li><b>Item name:<\/b> Project name + Task name<\/li>\n<li><b>Description:<\/b> Total logged time<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/li><li>All timesheets individualy &#8211; Applied all billable timesheets from tasks &#8211;&nbsp;<strong>(Not applied if Billing type is Fixed Cost)<\/strong>\n<ol>\n<li><b>Item name:<\/b> Project name + Task name<\/li>\n<li><b>Description:<\/b> Timesheet start time + end time + total logged time<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tasks that&nbsp;will be billed<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Perfex CRM you have the ability to chose what tasks to bill when invoicing project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To see the tasks that&nbsp;will be billed click on&nbsp;<strong>See tasks that will be billed on this invoice<\/strong>, you can adjust per your requirements.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If task is note complete when you click See tasks that will be on this invoice on the right side you can see a message Not Complete. Another message is auto added there with red if the task dont have any timers but you want to bill the task. Check the image below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/invoicing-project-tasks.png\" alt=\"invoicing project\" class=\"wp-image-828\" width=\"580\" height=\"475\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/invoicing-project-tasks.png 614w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/invoicing-project-tasks-300x246.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/invoicing-project-tasks-60x49.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/invoicing-project-tasks-150x123.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><div class=\"st-alert st-alert- \">Tasks with future start date cannot be billed.<\/div><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Actually they can if you check them. By default the tasks with future start date wont be checked which is logical.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Notes<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>All billed tasks will be marked as finished<\/strong> (If any tasks found not finished) &#8211; No notification sent to assigned staff members.<\/li><li><strong>After the task is billed you cannot start timers or bill the task again<\/strong>. If is required to bill&nbsp;again you need to re-create the task.<\/li><li>If customer have different currency set then default currency the project currency will be the currency of the customer.<\/li><\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Invoicing project is recomended to do only from the project area via the Invoice Project button on the top right side to keep track of all invoices created for&nbsp;the project. Project Invoice Info There is 3 types of how the invoice items will be structure when invoicing the project. Single Line &#8211; Not applied if [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[3],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-827","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-projects"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/827","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=827"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/827\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=827"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=827"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=827"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}